WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:42.480 --> 00:44.520
[ Narrator ]
The future:

00:44.600 --> 00:46.880
The polar ice caps
have melted,

00:46.960 --> 00:49.560
covering the Earth
with water.

00:49.640 --> 00:53.880
Those who survived
have adapted...

00:53.920 --> 00:55.800
to a new world.

02:21.080 --> 02:23.680
[ Gargling ]

02:32.240 --> 02:34.080
[ Metal Clangs ]

04:56.600 --> 04:58.480
[ Whistles ]

05:13.600 --> 05:16.800
Bad luck, English.

05:16.840 --> 05:21.240
But the Slavers are producing
a good grade of poxy these days.

05:21.280 --> 05:24.040
Cost you a handful of dirt--
or maybe that wind chime.

05:24.120 --> 05:27.720
- What are you doin’ here ?
- Just waiting.

05:27.800 --> 05:30.720
Take your hand
off the sail.

05:30.760 --> 05:33.120
Take it off !

05:33.200 --> 05:36.920
I’ve seen your boat before.
Haven’t seen you.

05:37.920 --> 05:40.560
Took it legal.

05:40.640 --> 05:43.400
Previous owner was dead on the tiller
when I found it.

05:43.480 --> 05:46.280
You had another hour
before I traded up again.

05:46.360 --> 05:48.840
[ Laughing ]
Just improving my means.

05:50.280 --> 05:52.520
- Well, I owe you then.
- No, thanks.

05:52.600 --> 05:57.600
I got all the supplies I need.
Just came from an atoll.

05:57.640 --> 06:00.520
Eight days east,
if you’re interested.

06:02.600 --> 06:06.120
- Two drifters meet,
something needs to be exchanged.
- I know the code.

06:06.200 --> 06:08.720
But l’ll give you this one
for free.

06:10.240 --> 06:12.080
Nothing’s free
in Waterworld.

06:12.160 --> 06:13.680
Ha-ha. Yeah.

06:24.520 --> 06:26.720
Smokers.

06:26.760 --> 06:28.720
Just enough wind
to get away clean.

06:32.480 --> 06:34.400
[ Drifter ]
Forget the bag.

06:38.240 --> 06:41.920
It’s not worth it. You’ll never
make it with your sails down.

06:42.000 --> 06:44.400
Hey !
[ Laughing ]

06:44.480 --> 06:46.360
[ Gobbling Sound,
Laughing ]

06:55.800 --> 06:57.920
What can I say ?
[ Laughing ]

07:17.240 --> 07:20.440
- Joe, he’s goin’ for it.
- What the hell ?

07:25.280 --> 07:27.240
Never seen that before.

07:30.880 --> 07:33.080
Here we go ! Go !
Drive ! Drive !

07:38.000 --> 07:40.840
Faster ! Faster ! Whoo !

08:00.840 --> 08:03.040
Come on ! He’s gonna get it !
He’s gonna get it !

08:21.920 --> 08:24.080
- Pick her up !
- Get it ! Get it !

08:24.160 --> 08:26.080
[ Indistinct Shout ]

08:43.799 --> 08:45.640
[ Curses ln Hindi ]

08:51.840 --> 08:54.320
Oh, no !

09:00.920 --> 09:04.280
[ Shouting, Gunfire ]

09:05.280 --> 09:08.640
[ Screaming ]

09:38.720 --> 09:41.480
Inbound !
Straight out from the gates.

09:50.560 --> 09:52.440
English.

09:55.000 --> 09:58.880
Flag’s down, drifter.
We got enough traders.

10:04.800 --> 10:07.640
[ Murmuring ]

10:12.000 --> 10:14.560
Dirt.

10:14.600 --> 10:16.480
Open the gates !

10:54.040 --> 10:56.600
[ Man Coughing,
People Chattering ]

10:56.640 --> 10:59.360
[ Man ]
Bones to berries.

10:59.440 --> 11:01.440
Veins to vine.

11:01.520 --> 11:05.560
These tendons to trees.
This blood to brine.

11:05.600 --> 11:07.200
Too old she was.

11:07.280 --> 11:11.680
This woman does leave us,
recycled and enshrined...

11:11.720 --> 11:14.480
in the presence
of Him who leads us.

11:22.680 --> 11:25.840
[ Boys Chattering ]

11:31.840 --> 11:36.160
- [ Boys Complaining ]
- What is that ?

11:40.480 --> 11:42.760
You know me ?

11:42.840 --> 11:44.680
I know what you are.

11:44.760 --> 11:48.400
Good. Then you know if you
look for trouble while you’re here,

11:48.480 --> 11:50.440
you’ll find more
than you can handle.

11:51.680 --> 11:54.160
You got two hours.

11:56.640 --> 11:58.520
I’ll only need one.

12:08.240 --> 12:10.680
[ Boy ]
He’s comin’ over here.

12:15.880 --> 12:17.760
- Me.
- You each get one...

12:17.800 --> 12:20.240
if everything’s here
when I get back.

12:28.680 --> 12:30.480
- Pure dirt.
- [ People Murmuring ]

12:30.560 --> 12:32.840
3.2 kilos.

12:34.760 --> 12:37.840
How’d you come by
so much of it ?

12:37.920 --> 12:40.560
Another atoll
30 horizons west of here.

12:40.640 --> 12:42.680
Where’d they get it ?

12:42.720 --> 12:45.840
- They didn’t say.
- [ Man ] We heard about that place--

12:45.920 --> 12:48.360
that they was all killed.

12:50.080 --> 12:52.200
- That’s why they didn’t say.
- Smokers ?

12:52.280 --> 12:55.360
Maybe Smokers,
maybe Slavers.

12:56.720 --> 12:59.440
So what’s the word ?
We tradin’ or not ?

12:59.520 --> 13:04.040
We’ll tally it
like, uh, pure hydro.

13:07.480 --> 13:10.320
Works out to... 62 chits.

13:10.400 --> 13:13.080
[ Coins Clanging ]

13:13.120 --> 13:15.000
I want twice that.

13:15.040 --> 13:18.560
[ Onlookers Murmuring ]

13:18.640 --> 13:22.560
- I just want one sip of hydro !
- No, not ’til you tell me.

13:22.600 --> 13:25.720
She got inkings on her back.
I seen her.

13:25.760 --> 13:28.840
They say if you read
the marks on the child,

13:28.920 --> 13:32.240
they’ll lead ya
all the way to Dryland.

13:32.320 --> 13:35.280
- Dryland’s a myth.
- Some still believe.

13:35.360 --> 13:38.320
They say the Smokers
even got an eye out for her.

13:39.960 --> 13:42.880
Well, then, we’d better
keep it to ourselves.

14:05.600 --> 14:08.400
- Help you ?
- Yeah.

14:08.480 --> 14:10.640
- Where’s the store ?
- You found it.

14:16.160 --> 14:18.040
You don’t have much.

14:19.200 --> 14:21.760
You the man
with the dirt ?

14:38.560 --> 14:40.040
Skoal.

14:43.520 --> 14:46.000
- One more.
- Make it two.

14:46.080 --> 14:49.680
A man this rich will buy
for a fellow outwater, l’m sure.

14:49.760 --> 14:52.000
One.

14:54.360 --> 14:58.040
That’s an interesting
pair of boots you got.

14:58.080 --> 15:00.160
- Trade ?
- No.

15:00.240 --> 15:02.240
Shame.

15:08.680 --> 15:11.520
Enola.
Hey, what are you doing ?

15:11.600 --> 15:15.240
- No, you can’t do that.
- I need another piece.
I want to draw some more.

15:15.320 --> 15:17.840
I’ll get it to you.
Just stay in the back.

15:17.920 --> 15:20.920
With all those chits,
you could order up a bath.

15:20.960 --> 15:23.520
- Have you ever had a freshwater bath ?
- Why are you talkin’ to me ?

15:23.560 --> 15:25.440
Just being friendly.

15:30.480 --> 15:32.720
- Is that a tomato plant ?
- Yeah.

15:32.800 --> 15:34.880
You have a keen eye.

15:34.960 --> 15:36.960
Saw one in a picture.
How much ?

15:42.920 --> 15:44.800
Half your chits.

15:55.840 --> 15:58.840
- I’ll take them too.
- Take what ?

15:58.880 --> 16:01.800
- You bought everything.
- I’ll take them shelves.

16:04.200 --> 16:07.520
So, what did you see out there
in your 15 months ?

16:07.600 --> 16:10.000
- Such as ?
- An end to all this water.

16:10.080 --> 16:13.440
Askin’ the wrong person.

16:13.520 --> 16:15.440
- The one they buried today ?
- Uh-huh ?

16:15.520 --> 16:17.920
She found the only end there is.

16:22.880 --> 16:24.760
I’ve got a proposition
for you, Mariner.

16:26.560 --> 16:31.360
- I’m not staying.
- We’re not asking you to.
All we want is your seed.

16:32.600 --> 16:35.400
We can look to our own
for impregnation,

16:35.480 --> 16:40.640
but too much of that sort of thing
gets... undesirable.

16:40.680 --> 16:43.560
When she’s pregnant,
you go on your way...

16:43.640 --> 16:46.120
with all the supplies
you need.

16:46.200 --> 16:50.040
You don’t have anything.
You’re dying.

16:54.520 --> 16:58.080
No man stays out that long
and turns down a woman.

16:59.360 --> 17:03.440
- He’s hiding something.
- Maybe he’s a Smoker spy.

17:05.920 --> 17:07.920
[ Whistles ]

17:13.400 --> 17:16.560
When the elders say so,
you can leave,

17:16.640 --> 17:18.480
and not before.

17:36.840 --> 17:38.720
Gills.

17:39.720 --> 17:43.600
- Mutation !
- He’s a mutant !

17:43.680 --> 17:46.320
[ Screaming ]
My hand !

17:49.960 --> 17:53.520
[ Screaming ]

17:53.600 --> 17:56.960
[ Man Shouting,
lndistinct ]

18:00.960 --> 18:03.200
Throw the nets !

18:15.720 --> 18:19.560
[ Crowd Yelling ]

18:31.560 --> 18:33.440
[ Screams ]

18:33.480 --> 18:36.280
By what right--

18:37.640 --> 18:40.400
You pay me to keep the peace.

18:40.480 --> 18:42.320
This isn’t it.

18:42.400 --> 18:45.680
- He has killed one of ours.
- He was defending himself.

18:45.760 --> 18:49.320
- He needs to be destroyed !
- Kill him. Let’s kill him.
- That may be,

18:49.400 --> 18:52.560
but not here
and not like this.

19:23.360 --> 19:25.120
[ Boy ]
What is it ?

19:25.200 --> 19:27.080
Damn.

19:28.240 --> 19:31.320
It’s tied.
I can’t get it off.

19:34.680 --> 19:37.800
Open the gate.

19:40.400 --> 19:42.560
[ Laughing ]

20:07.800 --> 20:11.040
Is it a map ?

20:11.080 --> 20:14.600
- You’d tell me if you knew,
wouldn’t you, Enola ?
- Mm-hmm.

20:17.920 --> 20:20.720
- What are you drawing ?
- I don’t know.

20:22.080 --> 20:26.360
Helen, look. Look at
the prodigal child’s latest vision.

20:28.960 --> 20:31.760
[ Chuckling ]

20:31.840 --> 20:36.720
- How soon before we can leave ?
- I don’t have any idea yet
where we can go.

20:36.800 --> 20:40.000
I haven’t figured out
the tattoo on her back.

20:40.040 --> 20:43.520
I’m a stupid man.
The answer’s right there.

20:43.600 --> 20:45.520
It’s just beyond me.

20:48.440 --> 20:50.440
Maybe he knows.

20:58.760 --> 21:03.080
Oh, yes, I see.
They are webbed.

21:03.160 --> 21:06.760
One, two, three, four,
five, six, seven, eight, nine,
ten digits. That’s wonderful.

21:06.840 --> 21:09.720
They tell me, too,
that you have gills.

21:09.760 --> 21:14.240
Isotropic gills. Are they merely
vestigial or are they functional now ?

21:14.280 --> 21:17.680
My name is Gregor. I’ve just come
to pay you a little vi-- vi--

21:19.200 --> 21:22.320
Oh, my God.
[ Laughing ]

21:22.400 --> 21:25.320
I’m sorry.
I’m not laughing at you.

21:25.400 --> 21:28.320
I’m excited. Your gills.
They’re functional.

21:28.400 --> 21:31.880
Icthyus sapien.
You can breathe in the water.

21:31.960 --> 21:35.680
How deep can you go ?
Look, l’m only here...

21:35.720 --> 21:38.240
because I want to learn
more about you.

21:38.280 --> 21:40.160
[ Spitting ]

21:43.120 --> 21:46.360
You don’t like humans
very much, do you ?

21:46.400 --> 21:49.880
I can’t say that I blame you.
But tell me:

21:49.920 --> 21:53.400
- Are all of your kind as
bad-tempered as you are ?
- [ Slamming Cage ]

21:55.880 --> 21:58.240
- I have no ’’kind.’’
- Oh, fish rot.

21:58.320 --> 22:01.600
I’d be surprised if there
weren’t others, and if there aren’t,

22:01.640 --> 22:04.920
there will be eventually.

22:04.960 --> 22:08.160
Anyway, l’ve come here
because I need to ask you a question.

22:08.240 --> 22:12.000
Where-- Where did
your dirt come from ?

22:12.080 --> 22:14.400
Is it from Dryland ?

22:14.440 --> 22:16.480
Do you know what this is ?

22:18.360 --> 22:20.640
The ancients-- They did something
terrible, didn’t they ?

22:20.720 --> 22:24.320
To cause all this water.
Hundreds-- Hundreds of years ago.

22:24.400 --> 22:27.320
If I tell you,
will you open this lock ?

22:29.720 --> 22:32.480
I haven’t a key.

22:32.520 --> 22:35.160
- There’s a mooring cleat down there.
- What ?

22:35.200 --> 22:38.160
- Good as any key.
- A mooring cleat ?

22:40.160 --> 22:42.800
I won’t hurt anyone.
I’ll just leave.

22:44.080 --> 22:47.240
- I’ll be right back.
- [ Man ] Gregor !

22:47.320 --> 22:49.200
What’s your business there ?

22:49.280 --> 22:51.320
- Move along !
- I’m not a brave man.

22:51.360 --> 22:55.520
If you know anything about Dryland,
please tell me. Please !

22:56.800 --> 22:58.640
Don’t let it die with you.

22:58.720 --> 23:01.320
No, no, no, no.
Stop !

23:01.400 --> 23:04.920
[ Man ]
Gregor ! Move along !

23:38.360 --> 23:43.360
[ Elder ]
After considerable deliberation
of the evidence at hand,

23:43.400 --> 23:46.720
it is our decision
that this mute-o...

23:46.800 --> 23:49.920
does, indeed,
constitute a threat.

23:49.960 --> 23:52.800
Therefore, in the interest
of public safety,

23:52.880 --> 23:56.280
he is hereby sentenced
to be recycled...

23:56.320 --> 23:59.080
in the customary fashion.

23:59.160 --> 24:00.960
Proceed.

24:06.640 --> 24:09.360
I’m sorry.

24:13.000 --> 24:15.040
Bones to berries.

24:15.080 --> 24:17.600
Veins to vines.

24:17.640 --> 24:21.280
His tendons to trees.
His blood to brine.

24:21.320 --> 24:24.320
Too strange for life he was.

24:24.360 --> 24:28.640
This mute-o now does leave us,

24:28.720 --> 24:31.440
recycled and entombed,

24:31.840 --> 24:34.600
in the presence
of Him who leads us.

24:44.160 --> 24:48.680
Smokers !
Dead out of the sun !

24:51.720 --> 24:55.040
To your posts !

25:07.200 --> 25:09.080
[ Confused Shouting, Screaming ]

25:09.120 --> 25:11.920
[ Woman ]
Oh, my God ! Oh, my God !

25:21.840 --> 25:24.480
- Kill !
- There !

25:24.520 --> 25:26.680
[ Screaming ]

25:30.560 --> 25:34.040
[ Indistinct Shouting ]

25:34.080 --> 25:36.800
We are safe
behind these walls.

25:38.240 --> 25:40.120
- Aren’t we ?
- [ Indistinct Shout ]

25:45.720 --> 25:48.680
- [ Indistinct Shout ]
- Let me out !

25:50.280 --> 25:52.520
Let me out !
l’ll fight !

26:00.440 --> 26:02.280
[ Shouting Commands ]

26:20.760 --> 26:22.600
Give me the key
to the city now.

26:26.280 --> 26:28.520
Let’s go !
Let’s go ! Let’s go !

26:31.080 --> 26:33.880
Floor it !
Floor it ! Floor it !

26:49.200 --> 26:51.680
[ Woman Screaming ]

26:54.240 --> 26:56.480
Swab it ! Swab it !

26:56.560 --> 27:00.080
Goddamn ! More ammo !

27:13.880 --> 27:15.840
[ Smoker ]
Break down the door !

27:15.920 --> 27:17.840
[ Screaming ]

27:19.480 --> 27:22.440
- My God !
- [ Screaming ]

27:22.520 --> 27:24.800
[ Woman Thrusting Spear ]
Ha !

27:24.880 --> 27:26.880
[ Screaming ]

27:26.920 --> 27:29.800
We’ll have this atoll
in no time.

27:32.960 --> 27:34.840
Crank it !
Crank it !

27:38.720 --> 27:40.880
Look !

27:51.200 --> 27:53.800
[ Men Shouting ]

27:58.800 --> 28:00.920
Look out !

28:08.400 --> 28:11.240
[ Gunfire, Shouting ]

28:22.520 --> 28:24.360
Oh, no !

28:34.840 --> 28:37.520
You get that goin’ !
Fill ’em up !

28:43.960 --> 28:46.640
[ Smoker Yelling,
Atoll People Screaming ]

28:48.280 --> 28:50.240
[ Screaming ]

29:13.920 --> 29:17.120
- [ Gunfire ]
- [ Gregor ] Helen, come quickly !

29:17.200 --> 29:19.280
Helen !

29:28.240 --> 29:31.080
[ Man Screaming, Gunfire ]

29:46.120 --> 29:49.440
You’re not supposed to go yet !

29:49.480 --> 29:51.760
Infernal machine !

29:55.120 --> 29:57.760
Gregor. Gregor, wait !

29:57.840 --> 30:01.040
Helen, I tried. There was an accident.
I can’t make it stop. Hurry !

30:01.120 --> 30:04.400
You can make it if you try. Run !
Up those stairs. Run ! Quickly !

30:04.480 --> 30:08.520
- Wait ! Wait !
- I’ll throw you a rope. Run quickly !

30:08.600 --> 30:11.480
- Throw the rope now. Run, Enola.
- Slow down ! Wait !

30:11.520 --> 30:15.320
- Throw the rope. No ! No !
- Wait !

30:16.800 --> 30:18.880
- [ Enola ] Gregor, don’t leave us !
- Oh, no !

30:18.960 --> 30:21.120
I’m sorry !
It was an accident !

30:25.320 --> 30:28.920
Helen ! Enola !
Helen, l’m sorry !

30:37.560 --> 30:40.800
Shoot him.
Shoot him.

30:48.160 --> 30:50.800
[ Man Screaming ]

31:06.480 --> 31:09.800
If I let you out of here,
you’re taking us with you.

31:11.040 --> 31:12.960
Sure.

31:14.560 --> 31:16.720
Enola, get down.

31:18.320 --> 31:20.440
Here. Get over here.
Get down.

31:20.480 --> 31:22.360
Hurry !
Come on !

31:25.200 --> 31:27.440
Get the gate.

31:29.000 --> 31:30.880
[ Gunfire ]

31:52.320 --> 31:54.560
[ Groaning ]

31:58.800 --> 32:00.640
[ Man ] Run !

32:14.440 --> 32:17.120
[ Groaning ]

32:24.000 --> 32:25.840
[ Mariner ]
Hurry up !

32:25.920 --> 32:27.720
Kamikazes. Come on !

32:27.800 --> 32:30.000
[ Engine Revving ]

32:52.800 --> 32:55.200
[ Atollers Screaming ]

32:55.240 --> 32:57.160
That made a hole.

32:58.800 --> 33:01.800
[ Gunfire ]

33:08.320 --> 33:11.680
Find her !
Get the girl !

33:16.560 --> 33:18.560
There !

33:25.240 --> 33:28.400
Go get that guy !
Go ! Kill him !

33:32.320 --> 33:34.640
- Wow !
- Enola !

33:38.080 --> 33:40.920
- [ Grunting ]
- [ Gunfire ]

33:44.640 --> 33:47.560
- [ Mariner ] You’re too slow !
- Run to the other side.

33:49.360 --> 33:52.360
- [ Gunfire ]
- Come on !

33:55.440 --> 33:59.360
- [ Shrieks ]
- Grab on ! Hold on, hold on.

33:59.440 --> 34:03.200
- [ Gunfire ]
- [ Craft Shuddering ]

34:03.240 --> 34:05.200
I’m stuck !
I can’t make it through !

34:05.280 --> 34:07.920
- Let her go !
- [ Gunfire Continues ]

34:08.960 --> 34:10.800
Just drop her !

34:25.000 --> 34:28.639
Turn the wheel.
The wheel ! Turn it !

34:28.679 --> 34:31.400
[ Gunfire ]

34:31.480 --> 34:34.320
That ! Come on ! Push it !

34:34.400 --> 34:36.960
- I am !
- Hurry ! Now pull !

34:37.000 --> 34:40.760
Push it ! Push it hard !
Push it hard !

34:40.800 --> 34:43.719
Okay, okay ! Now pull this !
Pull this !

34:43.800 --> 34:47.120
Pull ! Pull it !
Hurry !

34:56.880 --> 35:00.000
- [ Gunfire ]
- Enola, jump.

35:02.240 --> 35:04.560
- Look at me. Jump ! Now !
- Okay !

35:20.640 --> 35:25.280
Well, excuse me ! Did I say anybody
could leave before the battle was over ?

35:25.360 --> 35:27.200
- Did I ?
- No ! No !

35:27.280 --> 35:29.600
Well, do somethin’.
I hate sails.

35:38.520 --> 35:41.600
Hey ! Can you steer ?

35:41.680 --> 35:43.520
Can I trust you ?

36:16.640 --> 36:20.080
Answer me this, somebody.
Why is that boat still firin’ ?

36:21.120 --> 36:23.680
- What’s that cousin’s name ?
- Chuck.

36:23.720 --> 36:27.760
- Hey, Chuck !
- [ Smoker Leader ]
He’s pulling him right into us.

36:27.840 --> 36:32.040
Maybe he doesn’t answer to ’’Chuck.’’
Call him ’’Charles.’’ Charles !

36:33.120 --> 36:37.000
Stop him ! Stop him !

36:41.720 --> 36:44.160
[ Screaming ]

36:44.200 --> 36:46.120
Charles !

36:47.880 --> 36:49.760
Adios, cousins.

37:33.760 --> 37:35.840
She’s here somewhere.
Keep lookin’.

37:35.920 --> 37:38.400
[ Screaming ]
Stop it !

37:47.440 --> 37:52.800
- What you got ?
- Couple of heartbeats over there.
Aren’t sayin’ much.

37:52.880 --> 37:56.800
If you’ll notice the arterial
nature of the blood comin’
from the hole in my head,

37:56.840 --> 38:01.000
you can assume that we’re
all havin’ a real lousy day.

38:01.080 --> 38:04.760
So here it is: I need to know
about that tattooed girl.

38:06.240 --> 38:08.480
First one that
tells me lives.

38:08.520 --> 38:13.120
- I saw a girl. I saw, I saw--
- It was-- Sh-She had
a big tattoo on her.

38:13.160 --> 38:15.240
[ Indistinct ]

38:15.320 --> 38:18.080
You won.
Start over.

38:18.160 --> 38:20.200
I saw a girl.
I’m not sure,

38:20.280 --> 38:25.040
but I think she got on that boat
with three hulls.

38:25.120 --> 38:29.280
- The boat that cost me
a thousand G’s of go-juice ?
- Yeah, the mute-o’s boat.

38:29.360 --> 38:33.120
- Mute-o ?
- Yeah. He got these slits here.

38:33.160 --> 38:36.400
Like-- [ Laughing ]
Like fish gills.

38:36.480 --> 38:38.640
He wasn’t really a man.

38:38.720 --> 38:41.280
A fluke of evolution.

38:42.760 --> 38:45.040
Oh, l’m sorry.
A fluke of, uh--

38:45.120 --> 38:47.400
- Evolution.
- I know !

38:47.480 --> 38:51.200
- No ! No, you said
you wouldn’t kill me !
- Did I say that ?

38:51.240 --> 38:54.240
- Witnesses, anybody, did I ?
- Yes, yes, yes ! You said--

38:54.320 --> 38:56.760
- You said it.
- Oh, I may have.

38:58.720 --> 39:00.560
I may have.

39:01.760 --> 39:03.760
- [ Gasping, Screaming ]
- [ Gunshot ]

39:06.840 --> 39:09.000
We get to the ’Deez,

39:10.240 --> 39:13.400
tank up that sky boat;
send it out on patrol.

39:14.600 --> 39:17.200
We gotta keep an eye out...

39:17.280 --> 39:19.560
for that ichthy-freak.

39:42.360 --> 39:44.320
You been there, haven’t you ?

39:48.960 --> 39:51.440
Dryland ?

39:51.520 --> 39:53.600
You know where it is.

39:54.520 --> 39:56.440
Yeah, I know where it is.

39:59.400 --> 40:01.960
And, uh-- And we’re going ?

40:03.040 --> 40:04.920
You and I are.

40:06.400 --> 40:09.440
The kid we gotta pitch
over the side.

40:11.200 --> 40:15.040
- What ?
- My boat’s tore up.

40:15.120 --> 40:17.520
I’m takin’ on water.

40:17.600 --> 40:20.880
I’d be lucky to get
half a hydro ration out of that.

40:20.960 --> 40:24.440
You know--
I said I won’t drink.

40:24.480 --> 40:26.960
For 12 days ?

40:28.480 --> 40:31.280
No. It’s better
one of you dies now...

40:31.360 --> 40:33.320
than both of you die slow.

40:33.400 --> 40:35.520
Wait. Wait.

40:35.560 --> 40:37.920
We saved your life.
We got you out.

40:38.000 --> 40:41.920
No, you got me out so you
could get out. We’re even.

40:42.000 --> 40:43.960
She can cook.
She can fish.

40:44.000 --> 40:46.200
- So can l.
- Then take my necklace.
Take my necklace.

40:46.240 --> 40:48.440
- I got better ones below.
- No, look !

40:48.480 --> 40:51.200
Oh.

40:51.280 --> 40:54.240
After what you went through
back there on the atoll,

40:54.320 --> 40:57.360
I can understand
why you would want to.

40:57.440 --> 40:59.360
But she’s a child.

41:09.920 --> 41:12.240
Is there something else then ?

41:17.440 --> 41:19.920
Enola ! Go below.

41:21.000 --> 41:22.880
Enola.

41:32.800 --> 41:36.000
Yeah. You said so yourself.

41:37.800 --> 41:40.440
Been out there a long time.

42:24.240 --> 42:27.160
Couple hours ago,
I was potential dirt to you.

42:27.200 --> 42:30.480
- We’re not like that.
- You all are.

42:35.840 --> 42:39.000
Know what I was really thinkin’ ?

42:39.040 --> 42:42.080
Why I don’t drop both of you
in my wake right now.

42:43.360 --> 42:45.800
You got nothin’ I need.

43:01.080 --> 43:03.360
You’re taking us to Dryland.

43:07.520 --> 43:10.240
Killing’s a hard thing to do well.

43:10.280 --> 43:13.600
- Believe me. I’m not
the one to start on.
- Both of us !

43:18.880 --> 43:21.360
How long you plan
to hold that on me ?

43:21.440 --> 43:23.520
As long as it takes.

43:25.960 --> 43:28.880
- Okay.
- No !

43:30.480 --> 43:33.480
Let me out of here !

43:33.560 --> 43:37.240
Where the hell are you ?
Don’t you touch my child.

43:37.280 --> 43:39.160
Come here !
[ Indistinct Shouting ]

43:40.400 --> 43:42.560
[ Groaning ]

44:25.400 --> 44:28.000
Okay, now don’t move, okay ?
There.

44:28.080 --> 44:31.360
Ohh. Oh, lookin’
real good, yeah.

44:31.400 --> 44:33.640
There. There.

44:33.720 --> 44:35.560
All done.

44:35.640 --> 44:38.520
Now, there may be some small problem
in depth perception.

44:38.560 --> 44:41.320
Well, it better not
screw up my short game.

44:43.680 --> 44:46.000
- Well ?
- [ Smokers ] Looks good.
I like it. Yeah.

44:46.080 --> 44:49.040
- I like it better than your real eye.
- Much better.

44:49.120 --> 44:52.480
- What do you say, Toby ? The truth.
- Looks like shit.

44:52.560 --> 44:55.360
That’s why I love children.
No guile.

44:59.480 --> 45:02.800
It does look like shit.

45:02.880 --> 45:04.720
And it feels like cold shit !

45:04.800 --> 45:07.200
Deacon ? What--

45:08.520 --> 45:11.520
I’m sorry. I-lt’s just that
there’s a problem in the pit.

45:11.560 --> 45:13.440
Maybe you should come.

45:18.720 --> 45:21.920
- Let’s drive.
- [ Chattering ]

45:27.360 --> 45:30.880
The pit. Don’t bother
with the scenic route.

45:30.920 --> 45:32.800
[ Deacon ] Drive !

45:33.880 --> 45:36.000
Hey, it’s drivin’ better.

45:47.480 --> 45:49.640
Get off !

45:50.680 --> 45:52.960
Get over there.
Get out of the way.

45:53.040 --> 45:55.080
All right, all right, all right.
Okay, okay.

45:58.200 --> 46:01.480
You guys are great.
Bless all you cousins over there.

46:01.560 --> 46:05.840
Keep up the good work.
Growth is progress. Growth is progress.

46:05.920 --> 46:10.400
Somebody !
Hey, up there !

46:10.440 --> 46:12.320
Take it off !

46:14.680 --> 46:17.880
- Yes.
- Your Deaconship.

46:17.920 --> 46:21.720
Hello. Good morning.
Or night,

46:21.760 --> 46:24.200
whichever the case may be.

46:24.280 --> 46:27.040
- What is it ? l’m a busy man.
- I thought you should know.

46:27.080 --> 46:29.640
We’re down to exactly...

46:29.720 --> 46:33.560
four feet, nine inches
of black stuff.

46:35.080 --> 46:39.560
- [ Spitting ]
- Thank you, sir.

46:39.640 --> 46:42.400
- How many G’s is that after refinin’ ?
- Maybe three refuelers.

46:42.440 --> 46:45.920
- We’ll burn through that in two lunars.
- Sweet Joe !

46:45.960 --> 46:49.440
Will somebody please tell me
what’s happened to this place ?

46:49.480 --> 46:51.480
We outgrowed it.

46:51.520 --> 46:55.240
All right, the only thing
that is important is the tattooed girl.

46:55.320 --> 46:58.560
We don’t spare any go-juice
findin’ her.

46:58.640 --> 47:01.600
We don’t waste it anywhere else.
You cancel all those tractor pulls...

47:01.680 --> 47:03.480
and all that stuff
until later.

47:03.520 --> 47:05.440
You got it ?

47:06.880 --> 47:09.600
Dryland is the mother lode.

47:09.680 --> 47:11.720
[ Laughing ]
On your toes.

47:13.120 --> 47:14.960
Excellent.

47:43.240 --> 47:46.400
- Hi.
- Move.

47:46.480 --> 47:48.760
Enola !
Enola, come here !

47:50.960 --> 47:52.800
Come on !

47:54.720 --> 47:56.600
Enola, come over here.

48:09.600 --> 48:11.280
Hey !

48:13.440 --> 48:17.800
- What are ya doin’ ?
- Decorating your boat. It’s ugly.

48:21.760 --> 48:24.800
- Where did you get this ?
- From down below.

48:24.840 --> 48:27.440
This is mine !
You don’t touch anything of mine.

48:27.520 --> 48:30.760
- I drew it for you.
- You don’t draw on anything.
You understand ?

48:36.120 --> 48:37.960
What--

48:40.120 --> 48:42.960
This is my boat.
I got it the way I like it.

48:43.040 --> 48:45.720
You take up space
and you slow me down.

48:49.480 --> 48:52.000
You know, she’s just a little girl.

48:52.080 --> 48:55.080
- She doesn’t know your rules.
- You wanna stay ?

48:55.160 --> 48:57.000
You teach her.

49:15.680 --> 49:17.760
Enola, what’d I tell you ?

49:22.840 --> 49:25.120
You’re not so tough.
You know that ?

49:29.280 --> 49:31.120
How many people
have you killed ?

49:33.800 --> 49:36.560
Ten ? Twenty ?

49:38.440 --> 49:42.880
- You talk a lot.
- I talk a lot ’cause
you don’t talk at all.

49:42.920 --> 49:44.800
Now how many ?

49:46.560 --> 49:50.120
- Including little girls ?
- I’m not afraid of you.

49:53.840 --> 49:56.960
I told Helen you wouldn’t be so ugly
if you cut your hair.

50:00.200 --> 50:02.720
In fact, you talk all the time.

50:02.800 --> 50:04.800
- It’s like a storm
when you’re around.
- Enola !

50:04.880 --> 50:07.360
Hey ! What are you doing ?

50:07.440 --> 50:10.440
- [ Enola ] Helen !
- [ Helen ] You bastard !
She can’t swim !

50:10.520 --> 50:13.280
Help me ! Helen !

50:14.880 --> 50:16.760
Helen, help me !

50:16.800 --> 50:19.320
Helen !

50:19.360 --> 50:21.320
[ Sobbing ]
Helen, help me !

50:23.560 --> 50:26.160
[ Gasping ]

50:29.480 --> 50:32.040
Helen ! Helen !

50:32.120 --> 50:34.560
Hold on !

50:34.600 --> 50:36.920
Look at me.
Look at me. Look at me.

50:37.960 --> 50:41.800
Oh, please, come back.
Please !

50:41.880 --> 50:45.240
Please ! Oh, please !

50:45.280 --> 50:47.160
[ Choking ]

50:49.840 --> 50:52.320
Hey ! [ Gasping ]

50:53.840 --> 50:56.120
Hold on.
Okay, almost...

50:57.600 --> 50:59.480
there.

51:09.120 --> 51:10.320
Thanks. I swear,

51:11.560 --> 51:14.040
if you ever touch her again--

51:14.080 --> 51:16.160
You son of a bitch.
Look at me.

51:16.200 --> 51:18.680
You will go to bed that night,
and you will never wake up.

51:18.720 --> 51:20.960
- Shut up.
- What ?

51:21.000 --> 51:23.840
- [ Helen ] Smokers ?
- Yeah.

51:23.920 --> 51:26.080
Can’t we outrun them ?

51:26.160 --> 51:29.960
- [ Engine Humming ]
- Not with my sail down.

51:47.360 --> 51:51.240
- What are you thinkin’ about ?
- That’s a nice touch.

51:51.320 --> 51:53.160
That’s them.

51:59.080 --> 52:01.840
Don’t hit the kid.

52:06.320 --> 52:08.400
[ Cackling ]

52:15.680 --> 52:18.440
Hey !

52:23.200 --> 52:25.200
Coward !

52:30.840 --> 52:33.000
[ Laughing ]

52:33.080 --> 52:35.320
Fuck !

53:01.640 --> 53:04.320
No !

53:06.160 --> 53:09.160
[ Groaning ]

53:15.560 --> 53:17.440
[ Indistinct ]

53:24.320 --> 53:26.160
Cut it !

53:34.160 --> 53:36.800
Come on ! Come on !

54:07.240 --> 54:10.360
[ Yells ]
All right. Okay.

54:42.880 --> 54:44.920
[ Gunfire ]

55:07.840 --> 55:10.960
[ Helen ]
Oh, l’m really sorry.

55:11.040 --> 55:14.080
I’m sorry.
But you didn’t give me much choice.

55:14.120 --> 55:16.960
Oh, I know.

55:17.040 --> 55:19.680
But you ran away.
I-- What ?

55:19.720 --> 55:23.400
What are you do--
No ! Please, no ! No !

55:28.000 --> 55:30.000
[ Grunting ]

55:32.120 --> 55:36.240
Don’t ever touch
anything on my boat again.

55:39.520 --> 55:41.440
She said she was sorry !

55:45.280 --> 55:47.960
That means you’re supposed
to say something back !

56:10.240 --> 56:12.160
- Did you say somethin’ ?
- [ Enola ] Mm-mmm.

56:34.960 --> 56:37.040
[ Deacon ] The child--
did he have the girl with him ?

56:37.080 --> 56:39.280
- [ Pilot ] Uh-huh.
- Seems to me if we launch now,

56:39.360 --> 56:41.400
we can cut him down
just about here.

56:43.160 --> 56:46.400
- If he doesn’t change course.
- Ah, it’s not likely.

56:46.480 --> 56:49.960
He’s a wily one,
that ichthy-demon.

56:50.000 --> 56:52.520
Yeah, if he knows
he’s been spotted,

56:52.560 --> 56:56.240
he’ll expect us to expect him
to change course,

56:56.280 --> 56:59.720
which is exactly why
he’ll keep his heading.

56:59.760 --> 57:02.880
The important question is,
where’s he heading ?

57:02.960 --> 57:06.360
And does he know
how precious his cargo is ?

57:06.440 --> 57:10.640
I say that he’s headed here,
and we take him here.

57:18.120 --> 57:21.280
[ Drifter Shouting ]

57:21.320 --> 57:23.440
- Drifter ?
- Mm-hmm.

57:23.520 --> 57:25.360
- [ Shouting Continues ]
- [ Helen ] Are we gonna stop ?

57:25.440 --> 57:27.280
- Look at the flag !
- His flag’s up.

57:27.360 --> 57:29.360
I thought you all
stopped for each other.

57:34.440 --> 57:37.000
Well... maybe he has some food !

57:40.360 --> 57:42.880
Don’t find many who follow
the rules anymore.

57:42.920 --> 57:45.640
Well, make it quick.
What’s your business ?

57:50.400 --> 57:52.320
Trade.

57:54.160 --> 57:56.080
You got any resin ?

57:58.520 --> 58:02.480
Resin ? He’s gotta be out of
his mind. He’s out of his mind.
I don’t have any resin.

58:02.560 --> 58:04.920
- [ Babbling ]
- You been outwater
a long time, haven’t you ?

58:06.680 --> 58:09.000
Must be jokin’ me, man.
Resin ! You don’t got enough.

58:09.080 --> 58:11.200
How ’bout food ?

58:11.240 --> 58:13.200
Could you say that again, please ?

58:13.280 --> 58:16.080
- How ’bout food ?
- Ah, yeah, food.

58:16.160 --> 58:18.560
Yeah, that’d be good, eh ?

58:18.600 --> 58:21.480
I haven’t eaten in, well,
you know, forever.

58:22.680 --> 58:25.040
Which one of you two is a cook ?

58:25.120 --> 58:28.640
’Cause I usually fall for the waitress.
[ Chuckling ]

58:28.720 --> 58:30.640
Like you said,
I don’t have much.

58:30.720 --> 58:33.800
Now listen, eh ? [ Mumbles ]
Let’s see. What do I have to do ?

58:33.880 --> 58:37.560
We can start with that wee orchard
you got over there.

58:37.600 --> 58:42.280
- [ Whooping ]
- All right, hold it there.

58:42.360 --> 58:45.640
- [ Mariner ] We can talk.
- [ Drifter ] Fair enough.

58:45.720 --> 58:48.560
[ Babbling ]

58:50.400 --> 58:52.680
It’s a nice rod, isn’t it ?

58:52.760 --> 58:55.680
I like that rod.
It’s a nice rod. [ Babbles ]

59:01.760 --> 59:04.440
Got yourself a wee harem
goin’ here now, do ya ?

59:10.760 --> 59:12.800
What you want for the women ?

59:12.840 --> 59:15.160
We’re not for sale.

59:15.200 --> 59:17.800
Not for sale ?
There’s no such thing as not for sale.

59:17.880 --> 59:20.040
’’Not for sale’’ !
Not for sale, eh ?

59:21.960 --> 59:25.320
- Are they a pair or would you
consider sellin’ ’em separate ?
- No.

59:25.400 --> 59:29.240
Our business is done here unless you got
some resin for sale you can part with.

59:29.280 --> 59:31.160
I told you once already,
I don’t have it.

59:31.200 --> 59:33.880
I-l-l don’t have it.
Don’t have it. Don’t have it.

59:33.920 --> 59:37.920
Haven’t seen neither for trade
in lunars now. Wait. Wait, wait, wait.

59:40.960 --> 59:43.200
I do have somethin’ that’ll
make you change your mind.

59:44.440 --> 59:47.920
Somethin’ that you can’t pass on.
[ Giggles ]

59:48.000 --> 59:52.120
I took it off
an Atoller refugee camp.

59:52.160 --> 59:54.040
The life savings
of the entire clan.

01:00:01.680 --> 01:00:04.560
Paper.
[ Babbles ]

01:00:04.640 --> 01:00:09.920
It’s paper. Have you ever
seen paper ? Look at it.

01:00:09.960 --> 01:00:11.840
Smell it.

01:00:13.480 --> 01:00:15.520
I been savin’ it
for a special trade.

01:00:18.520 --> 01:00:21.040
Don’t you do it.

01:00:21.120 --> 01:00:23.880
You know, maybe l’m talkin’
to the wrong person here.

01:00:23.960 --> 01:00:26.040
Whose boat is this ?
ls it your boat or your boat ?

01:00:26.080 --> 01:00:29.600
No. No, it’s his boat.
But he doesn’t own us.

01:00:36.280 --> 01:00:38.240
Half an hour.

01:00:38.280 --> 01:00:41.720
[ Mumbling, Babbling ]
Out of his mind somethin’ there.

01:00:41.760 --> 01:00:45.600
I got two pages in here, man !
I mean, l’d get half a dozen
girls with this, you know.

01:00:45.640 --> 01:00:48.200
Half an hour.

01:00:48.280 --> 01:00:50.320
- You tradin’ or not ?
- Don’t.

01:00:50.400 --> 01:00:52.280
Shut up.

01:00:53.760 --> 01:00:55.800
Okay.

01:00:57.320 --> 01:00:59.520
Forty-five minutes
with the wee one right there.

01:00:59.560 --> 01:01:01.920
I like to do the talkin’,
if you know what I mean.

01:01:03.560 --> 01:01:05.440
No !

01:01:06.440 --> 01:01:09.400
Fair. Come, come,
come, come, come !

01:01:09.440 --> 01:01:11.720
No. My boat.

01:01:13.560 --> 01:01:16.840
- Fair enough. Fair enough.
Good, good, good. Aye.
- Helen.

01:01:16.920 --> 01:01:20.320
- Sit down.
- Enola, just do as he says.

01:01:22.440 --> 01:01:24.480
[ Chuckling ]

01:02:04.680 --> 01:02:07.560
It’s been a while for me now.

01:02:07.640 --> 01:02:11.080
Guess it’s been
more than a while, actually.

01:02:14.120 --> 01:02:18.880
I’ve only got half an hour.
[ Repeating ] Half an hour,
half an hour, half an hour--

01:02:19.920 --> 01:02:21.760
[ Mumbles ]
Great, great, great--

01:02:21.840 --> 01:02:26.400
[ Gasps ] Ooh ! You’re so beautiful.
Aye ! Anyone ever told you that ?

01:02:26.480 --> 01:02:29.280
Give me that. What are you doin’ ?
lt’s just a game.

01:02:32.560 --> 01:02:35.400
Oh, l, um-- I, uh--
We was just playin’.

01:02:38.400 --> 01:02:40.360
The trade’s off.

01:02:40.440 --> 01:02:42.240
I changed my mind.

01:02:43.240 --> 01:02:46.120
Well, um-- Well,
you can’t do that.

01:02:46.200 --> 01:02:48.560
I mean, a deal’s a deal, eh ?

01:02:48.640 --> 01:02:50.400
I just did.

01:02:50.880 --> 01:02:52.600
Hey !

01:02:52.640 --> 01:02:57.000
She’s mine. Aye. No. No, no
I own her. But-- No.

01:02:57.080 --> 01:02:59.840
- Go on.
- Get, get, get.
Go, go, go. Good, good.

01:02:59.920 --> 01:03:04.160
But don’t go too far now.
This won’t take but a minute.

01:03:09.040 --> 01:03:14.200
I hate this boat.
I hate this boat !

01:03:14.240 --> 01:03:16.840
You bastard.

01:03:20.880 --> 01:03:25.600
You-- You’re pretty stingy for a man
who’s got everything, aren’t ya now ?

01:03:29.320 --> 01:03:31.440
Oh-h-h. Ohh.

01:03:38.160 --> 01:03:41.520
- [ Yells ]
- [ Crashing ]

01:03:41.600 --> 01:03:43.640
[ Drifter ]
Ah, you bastard !

01:03:43.680 --> 01:03:46.200
[ Banging, Crashing Continue ]

01:03:54.560 --> 01:03:56.520
Where’s me boat ?

01:03:57.760 --> 01:03:59.800
Where’s me boat ?

01:03:59.840 --> 01:04:03.760
[ Mumbling ]

01:04:06.800 --> 01:04:08.640
Help me to me boat.

01:04:10.120 --> 01:04:12.000
Ow ! Me boat.

01:04:14.080 --> 01:04:15.880
Me boat.

01:04:43.680 --> 01:04:45.520
[ Helen ]
What the-- No !

01:04:47.840 --> 01:04:50.040
Never catch anything
with this. It’s useless.

01:04:51.840 --> 01:04:53.680
[ Helen Gasps ]

01:04:55.640 --> 01:04:59.960
Look, l’m sorry.
You were right about the pole.

01:05:01.240 --> 01:05:03.600
You were right,
but we have to eat.

01:05:09.080 --> 01:05:11.000
Now I know
you can hear me !

01:05:11.040 --> 01:05:14.400
Now we can fish for ourselves.
You show us what to do.

01:05:14.440 --> 01:05:16.640
You must know how.
Even you gotta eat !

01:05:16.680 --> 01:05:18.960
You just sit there.

01:05:41.600 --> 01:05:44.440
- What--
- [ Mumbling ] I don’t know.

01:06:18.800 --> 01:06:20.640
Happy now ?

01:06:38.080 --> 01:06:39.920
You don’t like my singing,
do you ?

01:06:42.720 --> 01:06:46.600
Helen says you don’t like my singing
’cause you can’t sing.

01:06:52.440 --> 01:06:55.040
- Ever try and listen ?
- To what ?

01:06:58.000 --> 01:07:00.160
The sound of the world.

01:07:04.160 --> 01:07:06.960
- I don’t hear anything.
- That’s because you’re too loud,

01:07:07.040 --> 01:07:08.880
and you’re movin’ around
all the time.

01:07:08.960 --> 01:07:11.600
Try sittin’ still.

01:07:11.680 --> 01:07:14.560
Eyeball ?

01:07:28.360 --> 01:07:30.320
I wish I had feet like his.

01:07:33.280 --> 01:07:35.080
Then maybe I could swim.

01:07:35.160 --> 01:07:36.760
Enola.

01:07:40.280 --> 01:07:42.280
[ Burps ] Sorry.

01:07:46.800 --> 01:07:49.160
Never met a person
couldn’t swim before.

01:07:51.840 --> 01:07:54.560
I can’t.

01:07:55.760 --> 01:07:57.960
People say I was weird.

01:07:58.040 --> 01:07:59.880
Maybe they were right.

01:08:03.280 --> 01:08:05.600
Maybe they were right
about you too.

01:08:32.319 --> 01:08:34.200
Enola wanted to give you this.

01:08:38.319 --> 01:08:40.840
And this.

01:08:42.880 --> 01:08:44.920
She won’t take it again.

01:08:51.080 --> 01:08:53.920
You don’t look much like her.

01:08:53.960 --> 01:08:57.840
- Well, l’m not her mother,
if that’s what you’re asking.
- You act like it.

01:09:01.439 --> 01:09:03.560
What are those marks
on her back ?

01:09:03.640 --> 01:09:06.200
Nothing.
They’re just fanciful things.

01:09:07.439 --> 01:09:11.399
- Like what she draws ?
- She draws what she sees.

01:09:11.479 --> 01:09:14.200
She’s like a mirror.

01:09:14.240 --> 01:09:16.240
People on the atoll
thought she was a--

01:09:17.920 --> 01:09:20.560
Freak ?

01:09:20.640 --> 01:09:22.920
Uh-huh. Yeah.

01:09:23.000 --> 01:09:24.880
I just thought
she was special.

01:09:32.279 --> 01:09:35.920
I’m not givin’ it
to her. It’s just--

01:09:36.000 --> 01:09:37.680
A loan.

01:09:37.760 --> 01:09:40.600
Yeah. I’m not
givin’ it to her.

01:09:46.160 --> 01:09:49.240
Is Dryland beautiful ?

01:09:50.720 --> 01:09:52.960
You’ll see.

01:10:10.040 --> 01:10:14.760
[ Enola Laughing, Giggling ]

01:10:17.680 --> 01:10:20.000
- Enola ?
- [ Laughing ]

01:10:20.080 --> 01:10:22.000
Enola, what are you doing ?

01:10:22.080 --> 01:10:25.360
- Those monsters’ll kill her !
- No, they’re asleep now.

01:10:28.280 --> 01:10:30.320
Hands around my neck.

01:10:32.280 --> 01:10:34.640
Let the water tell your arms
and legs how to move.

01:10:34.720 --> 01:10:36.800
We’re goin’ down.
Hold your breath.

01:12:12.240 --> 01:12:15.120
- What is it ?
- What is it ?

01:12:17.120 --> 01:12:19.120
Barter outpost.

01:12:19.200 --> 01:12:21.080
You said we’d get
to Dryland today.

01:12:21.120 --> 01:12:24.160
Today. Tomorrow.
What’s it matter ?

01:12:25.720 --> 01:12:27.560
I need resin.

01:12:36.800 --> 01:12:42.000
- What is that ?
- It’s PortuGreek. Their own language.

01:12:44.840 --> 01:12:47.080
Or so I thought.

01:13:12.440 --> 01:13:14.600
Ah.

01:13:14.680 --> 01:13:17.880
There’s my girl. Yeah.

01:13:17.920 --> 01:13:21.440
Howdy, darlin’.
Come on in here now.

01:13:49.760 --> 01:13:52.040
- What’s going on ?
- Smokers.

01:13:55.320 --> 01:13:57.160
What the hell ?

01:14:00.600 --> 01:14:03.400
He’s spotted us.
Sound it !

01:14:03.480 --> 01:14:07.160
Sound it ! Sound it !
Sound it ! Sound it !

01:14:17.760 --> 01:14:20.240
Yahoo !

01:14:27.720 --> 01:14:30.680
[ Helen ] Enola !

01:14:38.880 --> 01:14:41.640
- [ Bullets Whizzing By ]
- [ Grunting ]

01:14:41.720 --> 01:14:43.640
Starboard side ! Now !

01:14:44.640 --> 01:14:46.520
Get in the chair !

01:14:52.600 --> 01:14:55.360
Watch it.
He’s clearin’ the net.

01:15:06.280 --> 01:15:08.360
Go to the helm.

01:15:10.080 --> 01:15:12.360
- Get the centerboard !
- Centerboard ?

01:15:12.440 --> 01:15:15.080
What centerboard ?
I don’t know what to do !

01:15:17.600 --> 01:15:19.560
It’s too late.
Over here !

01:15:32.040 --> 01:15:35.520
[ Screaming, Yelling ]

01:15:38.360 --> 01:15:40.240
No !

01:15:55.840 --> 01:16:00.520
Gimme that rifle.
Boy, if you wanna do somethin’ right,

01:16:00.600 --> 01:16:03.160
you’ve got to do it yourself.

01:16:03.200 --> 01:16:05.080
[ Whispers ]
All right.

01:16:11.360 --> 01:16:13.240
- I winged him.
- I say we load...

01:16:13.280 --> 01:16:16.320
all the go-juice onto one boat
and run the freak down.

01:16:16.400 --> 01:16:19.560
You can’t catch him in ten boats,
and you wanna send just one ?

01:16:19.640 --> 01:16:22.160
Well, I pray that you’re jokin’.

01:16:30.240 --> 01:16:33.160
Bring me the trackers.

01:16:37.720 --> 01:16:40.080
He’s hurt.

01:16:40.160 --> 01:16:42.400
It’s not what you think.
They weren’t after her.

01:16:42.480 --> 01:16:45.000
- I saw what I saw.
- What ?

01:16:49.200 --> 01:16:51.040
No more lies.

01:16:52.480 --> 01:16:55.560
- [ Shrieks ]
- What are the marks on her back ?

01:16:55.640 --> 01:16:58.200
People say it’s the way to Dryland.

01:16:58.240 --> 01:17:00.760
Dryland’s a myth !

01:17:00.800 --> 01:17:03.720
No ! You said so yourself
that you know where it is.

01:17:03.800 --> 01:17:05.640
You did.

01:17:09.680 --> 01:17:12.760
You’re a fool to believe in something
you’ve never seen before.

01:17:12.800 --> 01:17:17.080
I’ve seen it. I’ve touched it !
Dirt that was richer
and darker than yours.

01:17:17.120 --> 01:17:18.960
It was in the basket
we found Enola in !

01:17:19.040 --> 01:17:21.560
- It doesn’t exist !
- Well, how can you be so sure ?

01:17:21.600 --> 01:17:26.160
Because l’ve sailed farther than most
have dreamed, and l’ve never seen it.

01:17:28.000 --> 01:17:30.720
But the things on your boat !

01:17:30.760 --> 01:17:33.080
’’Things on my boat’’ what ?

01:17:33.120 --> 01:17:36.440
There are things on your boat
that nobody has ever seen !

01:17:36.480 --> 01:17:38.560
What are these shells ?

01:17:38.640 --> 01:17:41.640
And that reflecting glass ?

01:17:41.720 --> 01:17:45.920
And th-the music box ?
That--

01:17:45.960 --> 01:17:49.520
Well, if not from Dryland,
then where ? Wh-Where ?

01:17:52.280 --> 01:17:54.160
You wanna see Dryland ?

01:17:55.800 --> 01:17:57.640
You really wanna see it ?

01:17:59.240 --> 01:18:01.240
I’ll take you to Dryland.

01:18:08.280 --> 01:18:10.120
Get in.

01:18:15.840 --> 01:18:18.880
- Well, what about Enola ?
- There’s only air for one.

01:18:18.920 --> 01:18:21.160
- Get in the water.
- It’ll be all right.

01:18:26.560 --> 01:18:28.560
Don’t touch anything.

01:18:33.120 --> 01:18:35.000
Okay ?

01:21:57.440 --> 01:21:59.320
I didn’t know.

01:22:01.080 --> 01:22:03.960
All this time...

01:22:04.000 --> 01:22:05.880
I didn’t know.

01:22:05.920 --> 01:22:07.800
Nobody does.

01:22:15.520 --> 01:22:17.440
Can you get us outta here ?

01:22:17.480 --> 01:22:20.840
I’d say there’re
two chances o’ that.

01:22:20.920 --> 01:22:23.240
- Hey !
- No way and no how.

01:22:23.320 --> 01:22:26.880
Shoulda bought me
that drink. Come on !

01:22:26.960 --> 01:22:28.680
This way. Come on !

01:22:28.760 --> 01:22:33.400
[ Men Yelling, Cheering ]

01:22:35.160 --> 01:22:37.320
Proper introductions first.

01:22:38.400 --> 01:22:40.760
I’m the Deacon.

01:22:40.800 --> 01:22:44.840
[ Men Laughing ]

01:22:44.920 --> 01:22:49.440
If you don’t recall the face,
perhaps it’s ’cause I didn’t
always look like this.

01:22:52.440 --> 01:22:55.920
Now, ahem, I suspect
she’s somewhere real close.

01:22:56.000 --> 01:23:01.600
So we can tear this boat apart
lookin’ for her, but l’d rather
somebody tell me where she is.

01:23:01.680 --> 01:23:04.400
And the first one
that does that, lives.

01:23:04.480 --> 01:23:08.680
And the runner-up--
Well, actually, there are no runners-up.

01:23:11.200 --> 01:23:13.720
Oh, sweet Joe,
I love this part.

01:23:13.760 --> 01:23:16.520
Choose ’em. One, two.
Live or die.

01:23:17.960 --> 01:23:21.000
You know, personally,

01:23:21.080 --> 01:23:23.880
I’d rather shoot
the sperm-of-the-devil here.

01:23:23.960 --> 01:23:27.040
Huh ? But you know somethin’ ?

01:23:27.120 --> 01:23:29.520
I don’t think you’re gonna
tell me, are ya ?

01:23:29.600 --> 01:23:31.440
Huh ? Too bad.

01:23:32.520 --> 01:23:35.880
Come on, eh ?
What do you say ?

01:23:35.960 --> 01:23:37.800
She’s not your kind.

01:23:39.200 --> 01:23:41.600
You don’t even have a kind.

01:23:41.680 --> 01:23:45.640
If you say it,
he’ll still kill us both.

01:23:45.720 --> 01:23:48.680
[ Deacon Grunts ]

01:23:49.800 --> 01:23:51.680
Let’s not get ahead of ourselves.

01:23:53.600 --> 01:23:55.480
If you don’t tell me,

01:23:55.520 --> 01:23:58.000
I swear to Poseidon
I will torch your boat.

01:24:04.320 --> 01:24:07.680
Refresh my memory.
What happens when neither of ’em talks ?

01:24:07.720 --> 01:24:10.440
- Never happened before.
- Never happened before.

01:24:10.520 --> 01:24:13.040
[ Sighs ]
All right !

01:24:13.120 --> 01:24:18.000
If they won’t tell us where
she is, do ’em ! Both of ’em !
Kill ’em now ! [ Fires Gun ]

01:24:18.080 --> 01:24:20.840
- No !
- [ Helen ] No !

01:24:20.920 --> 01:24:22.760
So gullible !
Bring her here.

01:24:22.840 --> 01:24:25.160
[ Men Cheering, Shouting ]

01:24:25.240 --> 01:24:27.840
- Take and ye shall receive !
- [ Helen ] No ! Leave her !

01:24:27.920 --> 01:24:30.480
So ends your daily sermonette !
[ Laughing ]

01:24:30.560 --> 01:24:34.240
All we gotta do is figure out this map.
Turn her upside down.

01:24:34.320 --> 01:24:37.520
-Does that mean anything to you ?
-No.

01:24:37.600 --> 01:24:40.960
[ Deacon ] We’ll figure it out back
at the ’Deez. Back at the ’Deez, boys.

01:24:41.040 --> 01:24:43.280
Careful with her.
Careful with her !

01:24:43.360 --> 01:24:45.160
- What about them ?
- Do ’em both.

01:24:45.240 --> 01:24:47.720
Torch the boat.

01:24:51.040 --> 01:24:53.840
We have to go under !

01:24:54.920 --> 01:24:57.680
No, I can’t breath like you !

01:24:57.760 --> 01:24:59.600
I’ll breathe for both of us.

01:25:23.200 --> 01:25:25.080
[ Man ] Whoo !

01:25:25.120 --> 01:25:27.000
[ Enola ] Helen !

01:25:28.960 --> 01:25:34.280
Helen, help !
Helen ! Helen !

01:26:04.160 --> 01:26:06.040
My boat.

01:26:15.080 --> 01:26:16.960
Enola.

01:26:17.000 --> 01:26:19.160
[ Door Opens ]

01:26:19.200 --> 01:26:21.920
What is this ?
Get those chains off her.

01:26:22.000 --> 01:26:24.800
What are we, barbarians here ?

01:26:24.880 --> 01:26:27.200
Goodness gracious.
Sakes alive.

01:26:27.240 --> 01:26:29.600
Come on. Outta here,
you big, nasty animal, you !

01:26:31.200 --> 01:26:33.520
Well, rub-a-dub-dub.
[ Chuckles ]

01:26:35.360 --> 01:26:38.600
You wanna come over here
and sit on my lap ?

01:26:38.680 --> 01:26:41.280
No ? Ahem.

01:26:41.360 --> 01:26:44.240
How ’bout a cigarette ?

01:26:44.320 --> 01:26:47.600
Nothin’ like a good smoke
if you miss your mom.

01:26:47.680 --> 01:26:49.520
Never too young to start.

01:26:51.080 --> 01:26:54.320
No. Well, I got somethin’
right here I know you’d like.

01:26:56.000 --> 01:26:58.440
Like to draw, don’t you ? Huh ?

01:27:00.360 --> 01:27:04.400
Huh ?
Now they’re yours...

01:27:04.480 --> 01:27:08.560
if you help me with just
one problem, all right ?

01:27:11.440 --> 01:27:14.880
Now, ahem-- Now that tattoo
on your back-- Ahem.

01:27:16.520 --> 01:27:20.800
I’ve been told that, uh--
that’s actually a map ?

01:27:23.840 --> 01:27:26.120
It’s the way to Dryland.

01:27:26.200 --> 01:27:28.040
Now we’re gettin’ someplace.

01:27:29.760 --> 01:27:32.440
Could you teach me
how to read that ?

01:27:35.200 --> 01:27:37.080
Setback.

01:27:39.200 --> 01:27:43.160
Well, have you ever heard
any of your friends talk about it ?

01:27:43.200 --> 01:27:48.160
You know, like your mommy or
your pet fish ? Did he say anything ?

01:27:48.200 --> 01:27:50.560
You shouldn’t make fun of him.
He wouldn’t like it.

01:27:50.600 --> 01:27:55.800
Girl, I don’t give a shit
what he’d like. He took out my eye.

01:27:55.840 --> 01:28:01.560
And if I ever see him again, l’m gonna
cut open his head and eat his brains !

01:28:01.600 --> 01:28:03.760
You think he’d like that ?

01:28:03.840 --> 01:28:07.440
Can’t kill him.
He’s even meaner than you are.

01:28:08.480 --> 01:28:10.560
But he’s not here.

01:28:10.600 --> 01:28:12.480
And he ain’t comin’.

01:28:12.520 --> 01:28:14.320
And no one’s gonna save you.

01:28:15.680 --> 01:28:17.520
He’ll come for me. He will.

01:28:17.600 --> 01:28:21.480
Then you better tell me what I wanna
know or he can see what’s left of you...

01:28:21.560 --> 01:28:23.640
in a goddamn jar.

01:28:33.520 --> 01:28:35.800
We’re going to die here,
aren’t we ?

01:28:54.880 --> 01:28:56.720
Aren’t we ?

01:29:05.760 --> 01:29:08.360
After the atoll,

01:29:08.440 --> 01:29:11.000
when I offered myself to you,

01:29:13.480 --> 01:29:15.840
why didn’t you take me ?

01:29:17.640 --> 01:29:19.520
’Cause you didn’t really want me.

01:29:21.400 --> 01:29:24.280
Not really.

01:31:15.280 --> 01:31:17.520
Have I been asleep long ?

01:31:23.000 --> 01:31:24.840
I was dreaming.

01:31:27.240 --> 01:31:30.120
It’s funny.

01:31:30.200 --> 01:31:32.800
I always thought Dryland floated.

01:31:32.880 --> 01:31:36.160
That it drifted with the wind.
That’s why it was so hard to find.

01:31:36.200 --> 01:31:38.400
Why did you believe in it so much ?

01:31:39.640 --> 01:31:42.080
Because we weren’t made for the sea.

01:31:43.360 --> 01:31:46.480
Got hands... and feet.

01:31:46.560 --> 01:31:49.080
We’re supposed to walk.

01:31:52.000 --> 01:31:53.840
I miss her sound.

01:31:56.280 --> 01:31:58.120
Don’t you ?

01:32:01.480 --> 01:32:03.280
[ Gregor ] Helen !

01:32:03.360 --> 01:32:06.400
He-- No, no, no.
Helen, up here. Above you !

01:32:06.440 --> 01:32:08.920
- [ Chuckling ]
- [ Helen ] Gregor !

01:32:08.960 --> 01:32:13.000
[ Chuckling Continues ]

01:32:13.080 --> 01:32:15.720
Smart thinking
to burn your boat.

01:32:15.800 --> 01:32:19.400
Without the smoke,
I never would have found you.

01:32:19.480 --> 01:32:21.440
Who’s that with you ?

01:32:21.480 --> 01:32:25.040
Ichthyus Sapien,
is that really you ?

01:32:25.120 --> 01:32:28.920
I’ll throw the rope down.
You catch it. I’ll help you climb up.

01:32:31.040 --> 01:32:34.400
Helen. Where’s Enola ?

01:32:34.440 --> 01:32:39.640
Smokers took her. They’d have me too
if it weren’t for him.

01:32:39.680 --> 01:32:43.720
My friend, thank you.
Very human of you.

01:32:45.600 --> 01:32:48.160
Go grab your things quickly.
Quickly. Come.

01:32:55.720 --> 01:32:57.680
[ Gregor ] You see ?
Right down there.

01:32:57.760 --> 01:33:00.640
There’s several of us survivors.
We’ll just start over again.

01:33:02.600 --> 01:33:04.480
[ Man ] You can’t ask us
to go get her !

01:33:04.520 --> 01:33:06.680
[ Woman ] Enola’s the reason
we’re in all this trouble.

01:33:06.720 --> 01:33:11.320
[ Helen ] They don’t have any
reason to kill her. They need
to find Dryland just like we do.

01:33:11.360 --> 01:33:15.200
- Of course.
- [ Helen ] lf the Mariner’s
willing to go, why not us ?

01:33:15.240 --> 01:33:17.280
[ Woman ]
lf he wants to go, then let him !

01:33:17.320 --> 01:33:20.440
[ Woman #2 ] We don’t want you here !
You or the girl !

01:33:20.480 --> 01:33:24.760
Helen. The papers
the Mariner brought you--

01:33:24.800 --> 01:33:29.280
It’s the same language the tattoo
is written in. They’re numbers.

01:33:29.320 --> 01:33:32.480
- [ Man ] Gregor,
you’re as crazy as she is !
- [ Woman ] We can’t stay here !

01:33:32.560 --> 01:33:36.000
We’re wasting valuable time.
More Smokers will come.
We need to be moving now !

01:33:36.080 --> 01:33:40.280
My friends, don’t you see we need
this child if we want to find Dryland ?

01:33:40.320 --> 01:33:42.240
- I’m not goin’.
- Nobody is.

01:33:42.280 --> 01:33:44.600
[ Woman ] We’ve seen their smoke
on the horizon !

01:33:44.640 --> 01:33:47.320
- Know what that is yet ?
- The numbers ? Yes, I think I do.

01:33:47.360 --> 01:33:52.680
It seems to be some ancient form
of geographic location:
latitude, longitude.

01:33:52.760 --> 01:33:57.400
It doesn’t make sense, though.
The numbers, they seem
to be backwards or something.

01:33:57.440 --> 01:33:59.520
- It’s upside down.
- The world ?

01:33:59.600 --> 01:34:02.120
The poles have reversed themselves ?

01:34:02.200 --> 01:34:04.360
I’ve been mappin’ the cities below.

01:34:07.040 --> 01:34:10.320
The world wasn’t created in a deluge.
It was covered by it.

01:34:10.400 --> 01:34:13.480
- [ Man ] That’s blasphemy !
- [ Helen ] No, it’s true.

01:34:13.560 --> 01:34:18.080
I’ve seen it with
my own eyes. There is land.
It’s right under our keel.

01:34:18.120 --> 01:34:20.160
- None of it’s dry anymore.
- Some is.

01:34:21.560 --> 01:34:25.960
Enola’s been there.
I know that now. I saw what she drew.

01:34:26.040 --> 01:34:29.720
So that’s why he’s going after Enola--
to find Dryland.

01:34:29.760 --> 01:34:32.360
I don’t care about Dryland.

01:34:32.440 --> 01:34:35.160
This is ridiculous.
Going after the Smokers ?

01:34:35.200 --> 01:34:37.400
He doesn’t even know
which direction they came from.

01:34:37.440 --> 01:34:42.080
- [ Man ] I say let him go.
- [ Woman ] We’re better off
without them anyway !

01:34:42.160 --> 01:34:45.760
If she’s alive,
l’ll bring her back to you.

01:34:45.800 --> 01:34:50.240
[ Woman ] Forget the mute-o, Helen.
If he brings her back, they’ll kill us !

01:34:50.280 --> 01:34:53.800
I can’t stand it. We gotta go help him.
I can’t ask him to do this alone.

01:34:53.880 --> 01:34:57.760
Oh, don’t worry, my dear.
You’re not going to have to.

01:35:03.600 --> 01:35:06.440
[ Deacon ] You got that tattoo
figured out yet ?

01:35:06.480 --> 01:35:09.000
It would be easier if it was flat--
big and flat.

01:35:09.040 --> 01:35:11.800
- It needs to be flat.
- What you got in mind ?

01:35:11.880 --> 01:35:16.040
Well, you cut it off her back.
You stretch it, mount it.

01:35:16.080 --> 01:35:19.600
- Give us a proper look.
- Take her down below until I holler.

01:35:19.680 --> 01:35:21.840
Saint Joe, we’re close.

01:35:24.000 --> 01:35:26.240
After centuries of shame.

01:36:00.880 --> 01:36:02.840
[ Scraping ]

01:36:10.320 --> 01:36:13.160
[ Distant Shouting ]

01:36:43.440 --> 01:36:46.840
[ Distant Laughter ]

01:36:49.560 --> 01:36:52.880
[ Crowd Shouting ]

01:36:52.920 --> 01:36:56.440
- They’re gettin’ ugly.
- Don’t I know it.

01:36:56.520 --> 01:36:58.480
Announce me, cousin.

01:37:00.120 --> 01:37:02.320
[ Crowd Chanting ]

01:37:02.360 --> 01:37:04.400
- [ Microphone Popping ]
- Hey. Here he is.

01:37:04.440 --> 01:37:06.320
[ Crowd ] Deacon !

01:37:06.360 --> 01:37:08.800
Rise up, brothers and sisters.

01:37:10.400 --> 01:37:13.680
Turn your eyes and open your hearts...

01:37:13.760 --> 01:37:16.080
to your humble benefactor,

01:37:16.160 --> 01:37:19.880
your spiritual shepherd
and dictator for life,

01:37:19.920 --> 01:37:22.800
the Deacon of the ’Deez.

01:37:22.880 --> 01:37:25.680
[ Crowd Cheering ]

01:37:38.880 --> 01:37:41.280
[ Cheering Continues ]

01:37:43.480 --> 01:37:46.480
- Look out !
- It’s mine ! lt’s mine !

01:37:46.560 --> 01:37:48.840
[ Confused Shouting ]

01:37:52.880 --> 01:37:56.080
- Deacon !
- Wahoo !

01:37:56.160 --> 01:38:01.680
Children.
Children of the provider.

01:38:01.760 --> 01:38:05.480
Citizens of the good ship.
Please now, hear me speak.

01:38:09.320 --> 01:38:12.280
- I’ve had a vision.
- [ Man ] Yeah, we’re
tired of your visions !

01:38:12.360 --> 01:38:14.640
What about the land
you promised us ?

01:38:14.680 --> 01:38:17.360
[ Crowd ]
Yeah ! Yeah !

01:38:17.400 --> 01:38:19.520
[ Deacon ]
O ye of little faith.

01:38:19.600 --> 01:38:21.760
I’ve had a vision so great...

01:38:21.840 --> 01:38:25.080
that as it came to me, I wept.

01:38:25.160 --> 01:38:29.120
- And in this splenditudinous
figment of wonder,
- Is that Bone’s ride ?

01:38:29.200 --> 01:38:31.200
- Is that blood on the seat ?
- I saw--

01:38:31.280 --> 01:38:34.960
And you know
what it is that I saw.

01:38:35.040 --> 01:38:38.800
I saw... the land.

01:38:38.840 --> 01:38:41.720
[ Cheering ]

01:38:48.680 --> 01:38:52.080
[ Gasping ]

01:39:02.960 --> 01:39:05.040
[ Crowd Chanting ]

01:39:10.520 --> 01:39:12.600
- Horse, that you ?
- [ Engine Revving ]

01:39:17.080 --> 01:39:20.080
Look, just bring it in slow,
okay ? I don’t have all day.

01:39:20.160 --> 01:39:23.400
- [ Engine Revs ]
- Horse !

01:39:23.440 --> 01:39:25.840
Just bring it up slow.

01:39:26.920 --> 01:39:29.680
I said slow !
[ Screams ]

01:39:34.280 --> 01:39:38.120
Shouldn’t be doing that.
You’re gonna get in trouble.

01:39:38.160 --> 01:39:40.360
Ha. That’s right.

01:39:40.400 --> 01:39:44.280
You’re not afraid. You’ve got
your pet freak comin’ to rescue you.

01:39:44.360 --> 01:39:48.720
He’s not a freak,
and he can take you anytime.

01:39:48.800 --> 01:39:52.720
He’s killed dozens of people, and he
doesn’t have any mercy or anything.

01:39:52.800 --> 01:39:54.840
He even kills little girls.

01:39:56.640 --> 01:39:58.160
Haven’t we all ?

01:40:00.160 --> 01:40:02.080
Shit.

01:40:02.160 --> 01:40:04.240
It’s Horse.

01:40:05.520 --> 01:40:07.920
- Find him. Find him !
- Come on !

01:40:08.000 --> 01:40:12.120
- [ Crowd Chanting ]
- Yes ! Yes ! Yes !

01:40:12.200 --> 01:40:15.720
- Come on.
- Gettin’ nervous, aren’t you ?

01:40:19.840 --> 01:40:21.680
I don’t get nervous.

01:40:22.960 --> 01:40:25.360
[ Deacon ]
And if there’s a river, we’ll dam it.

01:40:25.440 --> 01:40:29.720
And if there’s a tree,
we’ll ram it.

01:40:29.800 --> 01:40:32.800
’Cause l’m talkin’ progress here.

01:40:32.880 --> 01:40:35.760
Yes, sir. I’m talkin’ development.

01:40:35.840 --> 01:40:39.720
- [ Man ] Yeah !
- For we shall suck and savor...

01:40:39.760 --> 01:40:44.040
the sweet flavor of Dryland.

01:40:44.080 --> 01:40:45.880
- [ Crowd Whistling ]
- [ Enola ] Face is all red.

01:40:45.960 --> 01:40:50.840
- [ Deacon Continues Faintly ]
- Helen said with anybody
that has a face that red,

01:40:50.920 --> 01:40:53.000
he’s had too much sun
or too much to drink.

01:40:53.040 --> 01:40:57.000
- All right, that’s it.
I’m gonna burn your face.
- Almost time.

01:40:57.040 --> 01:41:01.000
- [ Clanging ]
- What’s up ?
- We’re just talkin’ about our friend.

01:41:03.240 --> 01:41:06.000
- [ Doctor ] What’s his name ?
- [ Enola ] He doesn’t have a name.

01:41:06.040 --> 01:41:08.560
So death can’t find him.

01:41:08.600 --> 01:41:10.480
Nah-nah.

01:41:13.600 --> 01:41:17.360
Doesn’t have a home
or people to care for.

01:41:17.440 --> 01:41:20.240
He’s not afraid of anything,
men least of all.

01:41:20.320 --> 01:41:23.800
He’s fast and strong
like a big wind.

01:41:23.880 --> 01:41:26.960
He can hear a hundred miles
and see a hundred miles underwater.

01:41:27.040 --> 01:41:30.920
- [ Gagging ]
- He can hide in the shadow
of the noon sun.

01:41:30.960 --> 01:41:34.720
He could be right behind you, and you
won’t even know it ’til you’re dead !

01:41:37.200 --> 01:41:39.120
Give it a rest.

01:41:40.360 --> 01:41:42.320
He’ll come for me. He will.

01:41:42.360 --> 01:41:44.880
- [ Deacon Addressing Crowd ]
We are the people--
- Yeah ?

01:41:44.920 --> 01:41:48.240
- Well, I hope he does.
- [ Deacon ] The Lord’s creation.

01:41:49.480 --> 01:41:51.320
Remember you said that.

01:41:52.400 --> 01:41:55.080
[ Deacon Continues ]
Look at us.

01:41:55.120 --> 01:41:57.680
- Look at us here today.
- [ Man ] Yeah !

01:41:57.720 --> 01:42:01.200
Dryland is not just
our destination,

01:42:01.280 --> 01:42:03.280
but it is our destiny !

01:42:03.360 --> 01:42:05.560
[ Cheering, Whistling ]

01:42:12.280 --> 01:42:14.640
Find him. Find him !

01:42:14.720 --> 01:42:16.800
How can I find...

01:42:16.880 --> 01:42:18.920
this glorious place ?

01:42:19.920 --> 01:42:22.640
And he said to me:

01:42:22.680 --> 01:42:26.480
’’A child shall lead you.’’

01:42:27.920 --> 01:42:29.960
A child.

01:42:30.000 --> 01:42:32.240
- And behold !
- It’s time.

01:42:32.280 --> 01:42:35.240
The instrument of our salvation !

01:42:35.280 --> 01:42:38.960
[ Crowd Cheering ]

01:42:42.440 --> 01:42:44.760
[ Deacon ]
Our guide in the wild.

01:42:44.840 --> 01:42:47.120
[ Deacon ]
Our beacon in the darkness.

01:42:47.200 --> 01:42:49.040
Turn her around, Nord.

01:42:49.120 --> 01:42:51.800
She has shown me the path !

01:42:51.880 --> 01:42:54.320
[ Cheering ]

01:42:56.080 --> 01:42:59.440
And before the holy-most moment
is upon us,

01:42:59.480 --> 01:43:02.800
Iet’s sacrifice one
to old Saint Joe.

01:43:05.840 --> 01:43:09.320
And let’s get this
tub of shit up to speed.

01:43:15.120 --> 01:43:17.040
Yep.

01:43:24.400 --> 01:43:27.200
[ Wild Cheering ]

01:43:53.480 --> 01:43:55.320
Pull !

01:43:55.400 --> 01:43:57.960
- Pull !
- Pull !

01:43:58.000 --> 01:44:00.080
- Pull.
- Pull !

01:44:14.000 --> 01:44:15.840
Ow.

01:44:19.240 --> 01:44:22.400
- So which way we rowin’ ?
- I don’t have a goddamn clue.

01:44:22.480 --> 01:44:24.320
[ Laughs ]
Don’t worry.

01:44:24.400 --> 01:44:27.240
They’ll row for a month
before they figure out l’m fakin’ it.

01:44:27.280 --> 01:44:29.840
But, um, wh-wh--

01:44:29.920 --> 01:44:32.920
Oh, you want details.
Well, l’m not tellin’ these savages...

01:44:33.000 --> 01:44:35.120
that we haven’t
solved the map yet.

01:44:35.160 --> 01:44:40.360
I promised them results,
and l’ll get ’em if I gotta
cut ’em out of her goddamn back.

01:44:41.760 --> 01:44:45.000
Who is that ?
Who is that ?

01:44:46.040 --> 01:44:48.400
Maybe one of
the spare rowers ?

01:44:56.000 --> 01:44:58.640
Why aren’t you rowin’ ?

01:45:06.840 --> 01:45:08.880
- It’s him.
- It is him.

01:45:10.200 --> 01:45:12.760
You guys are in
so much trouble.

01:45:15.480 --> 01:45:19.680
Well, l’ll be damned.
It’s the gentleman guppy.

01:45:19.760 --> 01:45:23.400
You know, he’s like
a turd that won’t flush.

01:45:23.440 --> 01:45:26.000
I want the girl.

01:45:28.320 --> 01:45:33.280
You know, I thought you
were stupid, friend.

01:45:33.360 --> 01:45:36.160
- [ Gun Cocking ]
- But I underestimated you.

01:45:36.240 --> 01:45:39.120
You’re a total freakin’ retard.

01:45:39.200 --> 01:45:42.160
[ Laughing ]

01:45:42.200 --> 01:45:45.320
I want the girl. That’s all.

01:45:45.360 --> 01:45:50.000
Well, what on this screwed-up Earth
makes you think you’re gonna get her ?

01:45:57.920 --> 01:45:59.760
You know what this is ?

01:46:03.920 --> 01:46:06.320
I drop it, you burn.

01:46:06.400 --> 01:46:10.160
- We all burn.
- Now wait, wait, wait, wait.

01:46:10.200 --> 01:46:13.880
Ahem. Let’s not do
anything rash here.

01:46:13.960 --> 01:46:17.040
I mean, uh, are you sure
she’s worth all this ?

01:46:17.080 --> 01:46:20.120
She never does stop talkin’.
She never shuts up.

01:46:20.200 --> 01:46:22.440
- I noticed.
- What is it then ?

01:46:22.480 --> 01:46:24.720
Huh ? lt’s the map.

01:46:26.160 --> 01:46:28.840
She’s my friend.

01:46:28.880 --> 01:46:31.560
Golly gee.
A single tear rolls down my cheek.

01:46:31.600 --> 01:46:34.440
I mean, you’re gonna
die for your friend.

01:46:35.760 --> 01:46:37.640
If it comes to that.

01:46:39.840 --> 01:46:44.080
- He’s bluffing. I’ll kill him.
- He’s not bluffing. He never bluffs.

01:46:44.160 --> 01:46:45.320
Shut up !

01:46:46.600 --> 01:46:51.560
I don’t-- I-l-- I don’t think
you’re gonna drop that torch, my friend.

01:46:51.600 --> 01:46:55.120
- Why not ?
- Because you’re not crazy.

01:46:58.520 --> 01:47:01.200
No !

01:47:07.880 --> 01:47:10.480
Oh, thank God.

01:47:14.120 --> 01:47:16.720
[ Screaming ]

01:47:21.760 --> 01:47:24.760
[ Gunfire ]

01:47:26.720 --> 01:47:28.920
[ Smoker ]
Look out ! [ Screaming ]

01:47:29.000 --> 01:47:31.400
Get him !

01:47:31.440 --> 01:47:34.800
Let’s go, goddamn it !

01:47:34.880 --> 01:47:39.440
- [ Screaming ]
- Don’t just stand there !
Kill somethin’ !

01:47:42.480 --> 01:47:44.320
Was this your big vision ?

01:47:48.120 --> 01:47:50.920
[ Screaming ]

01:47:52.680 --> 01:47:56.440
Oh, yeah ! l’ve always wanted
to drive this monster.

01:47:59.600 --> 01:48:02.640
There he is !
There he is !

01:48:05.600 --> 01:48:07.880
That’s him ! There !

01:48:10.000 --> 01:48:12.400
[ Shrieks ]

01:48:14.680 --> 01:48:17.560
[ Screaming ]

01:48:20.240 --> 01:48:23.720
[ Enola ]
No ! Let go !

01:48:29.280 --> 01:48:31.120
[ Explosion ]

01:48:33.000 --> 01:48:35.280
[ Enola ]
Let go !

01:48:38.560 --> 01:48:41.040
- [ Enola ] Let me go ! Let go !
- [ Deacon ] Pilot !

01:48:41.080 --> 01:48:43.440
- [ Deacon ] Pilot !
- [ Enola ] Let me go !

01:48:43.520 --> 01:48:45.360
- [ Mariner Cocking Gun ]
- Let go !

01:48:45.440 --> 01:48:47.320
Let go-o-o-o !

01:48:49.520 --> 01:48:52.320
[ Laughing ]
You should’ve stayed underwater.

01:48:52.400 --> 01:48:55.160
[ Clicks Twice ]

01:48:57.520 --> 01:49:00.120
Oh !

01:49:01.680 --> 01:49:05.840
Now you know how to fly an airplane ?
You’re lucky I do.

01:49:05.920 --> 01:49:08.800
Ow ! Now you stop it !
You behave yourself now !

01:49:38.560 --> 01:49:40.720
[ Explosions ]

01:50:01.600 --> 01:50:04.520
- Oh !
- [ Mariner Grunting ]

01:50:16.520 --> 01:50:18.640
[ Explosion ]

01:50:30.960 --> 01:50:32.840
[ Explosion ]

01:50:37.480 --> 01:50:39.320
[ Helen ]
lt’s going down.

01:50:39.400 --> 01:50:44.400
- You can see it sinking.
- Gregor, bring us
right down on top of it.

01:50:44.440 --> 01:50:46.520
- Hurry, Gregor !
- [ Gregor ] Don’t worry.

01:50:46.600 --> 01:50:48.440
Hurry.

01:50:52.240 --> 01:50:55.160
[ Clanging, Rumbling ]

01:50:59.720 --> 01:51:02.760
Enola ! Up here !

01:51:02.800 --> 01:51:04.720
Grab on !

01:51:09.600 --> 01:51:11.480
[ Gregor ]
Are they on yet ?

01:51:14.720 --> 01:51:17.400
- [ Gregor ] What is it ?
- [ Helen ] I don’t know !

01:51:17.480 --> 01:51:19.200
No !

01:51:28.080 --> 01:51:33.280
Gotcha ! l’m gonna rip
your cute little lungs out.

01:51:36.800 --> 01:51:38.680
[ Yelling ]

01:51:42.000 --> 01:51:44.520
[ Enraged Shout ]

01:51:46.960 --> 01:51:49.400
Pull ! Almost.

01:51:53.080 --> 01:51:55.600
[ Helen, Gregor Laughing ]

01:51:56.920 --> 01:52:00.440
[ Explosion ]

01:52:26.880 --> 01:52:28.560
- [ Shrieks ]
- [ Helen ] No !

01:52:28.600 --> 01:52:31.440
- [ Enola Screaming ]
- [ Helen ] No ! Enola !

01:52:32.720 --> 01:52:35.080
Saint Joe.
Hole in one.

01:52:35.120 --> 01:52:38.800
- Helen !
- [ Helen ] No ! Enola !
- [ Gregor ] Helen !

01:52:38.840 --> 01:52:41.400
Hey ! Hey !

01:52:47.720 --> 01:52:51.600
Ohh. Oh, no ! Quick !
What are we gonna do ?

01:52:51.640 --> 01:52:54.680
Hyah ! Hyah !

01:52:54.760 --> 01:52:57.200
Tie this off.

01:53:00.480 --> 01:53:03.160
- [ Gregor ] Hurry !
- Tie it !

01:53:07.560 --> 01:53:10.000
- Got it !
- [ Enola ] Ah !

01:53:13.760 --> 01:53:15.560
[ Screaming ]

01:53:22.320 --> 01:53:24.760
Get ’em up now.

01:53:31.120 --> 01:53:34.360
- [ Enola Grunting ]
- [ Gregor Laughing ]

01:53:34.440 --> 01:53:37.720
- [ Gregor ] Of course !
North is south.
- What ?

01:53:37.800 --> 01:53:41.040
- South is north.
- I was swimming.

01:53:41.080 --> 01:53:43.240
- I saw.
- [ Gregor ] My friends.

01:53:43.280 --> 01:53:45.320
My friends, look.

01:53:45.360 --> 01:53:50.000
If I take a bearing from the sun and
reverse the coordinates on Enola’s back,

01:53:51.960 --> 01:53:55.040
then Dryland is that way !

01:55:00.120 --> 01:55:02.840
[ Sea Gull Chattering ]

01:55:51.440 --> 01:55:54.360
- [ Helen Laughing ]
- It’s fresh !

01:55:54.440 --> 01:55:57.000
All of this !
lt’s fresh !

01:55:57.040 --> 01:55:58.960
[ Helen Shrieks ]

01:55:59.000 --> 01:56:03.840
[ Laughing ]

01:56:03.920 --> 01:56:05.760
No !
[ Laughing ]

01:56:10.120 --> 01:56:12.400
[ Helen ]
Whoo ! Whoo !

01:56:12.440 --> 01:56:14.680
I found something !

01:56:26.800 --> 01:56:30.280
Maybe we should put them
under the dirt.

01:56:30.320 --> 01:56:32.200
I think it was their way.

01:56:34.360 --> 01:56:36.240
[ Gregor ] They must have known
they were dying.

01:56:36.320 --> 01:56:38.160
[ Helen Laughing ]

01:56:58.160 --> 01:57:00.040
[ Winding Key ]

01:57:05.640 --> 01:57:07.480
I’m home.

01:57:17.960 --> 01:57:20.400
- Where’s the Mariner ?
- He was outside.

01:57:25.520 --> 01:57:28.080
Wait. Wait !
I want to show you this.

01:57:28.120 --> 01:57:30.960
[ Birds Chirping Loudly ]

01:57:42.680 --> 01:57:45.920
[ Hoofbeats ]

01:57:48.480 --> 01:57:52.200
[ Whinnying ]

01:58:01.240 --> 01:58:04.360
[ Birds Twittering, Chirping ]

01:58:37.600 --> 01:58:40.160
First time in your life
you got nothin’ to say ?

01:58:54.360 --> 01:58:56.880
Enola, I have to go now.

01:58:56.920 --> 01:58:58.800
But you came back for me.

01:59:00.800 --> 01:59:02.640
I like you.

01:59:07.600 --> 01:59:09.480
Why are you leaving ?

01:59:12.160 --> 01:59:15.680
- I don’t belong here.
I belong out there.
- You belong here.

01:59:18.880 --> 01:59:21.640
It’s too strange here.
It doesn’t move right.

01:59:21.680 --> 01:59:24.400
Helen said that
it’s only land sickness.

01:59:25.600 --> 01:59:29.000
We’re all feeling it.
It’ll go away soon.

01:59:29.040 --> 01:59:30.920
It’s more than that.

